    "what_description": "Pygeum africanum is a deciduous shrub or small tree native to tropical Africa, belonging to the family Rosaceae. It grows up to 10 meters in height, with a broad, rounded crown and grayish-brown bark, and has simple, alternate, elliptical leaves that are 2-5 centimeters long and 1-3 centimeters wide. The leaves are dark green on top and pale underneath, with a leathery texture and a double serrated margin. The plant produces small, greenish-yellow flowers in clusters, and produces 1-2 centimeter long red or yellowish berries. The bark of the plant contains a resinous extract that is used in traditional medicine to treat urinary problems and is also used in modern herbal medicine.",
