    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Pygeum africanum are benign prostatic hyperplasia, urinary retention, and urinary incontinence, which are characterized by the enlargement of the prostate gland leading to reduced urine flow and involuntary loss of urine, respectively. Pygeum africanum has been shown to improve symptoms of prostatitis, a condition of inflammation of the prostate gland, through its anti-inflammatory properties. In addition, it has been proven to be effective in treating erectile dysfunction, a condition characterized by the inability to achieve or maintain an erection, by increasing testosterone levels and improving blood flow to the penis. It is also effective in treating overactive bladder, nocturia, urinary tract infections, and urinary frequency, which are characterized by the sudden need to urinate, frequent urination at night, and the presence of bacteria in the urinary tract, respectively. Furthermore, Pygeum africanum has been found to improve symptoms of lower urinary tract symptoms, pollakiuria, lower back pain, and cystitis, but has shown limited effectiveness in treating enlarged prostate, kidney stones, urinary urgency, prostatic cancer, hair loss, and acne.",
