    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Pygeum africanum are rooted in its ability to exhibit anti-inflammatory effects, which contribute to its potential in reducing the severity of conditions such as prostatitis and benign prostatic hyperplasia. The antioxidant properties of Pygeum africanum have been shown to scavenge free radicals and mitigate oxidative stress, thereby protecting the brain from neurodegenerative diseases like Alzheimer's and Parkinson's. Additionally, Pygeum africanum has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, which are attributed to the presence of triterpenes and flavonoids that inhibit the growth of pathogens. The androgenic properties of Pygeum africanum are also noteworthy, as the plant's saponins and sterols have been found to stimulate the production of testosterone, thereby supporting prostate health. Furthermore, the presence of volatile oils and phenolic compounds in Pygeum africanum contributes to its neuroprotective effects, which may help to prevent or slow the progression of neurodegenerative diseases.",
