    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Pygeum africanum are ursolic acid, oleanolic acid, and a variety of sterols including \u03b2-sitosterol, campesterol, and stigmasterol, which have been shown to inhibit 5-alpha-reductase, an enzyme involved in the development of benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). Lupeol, a pentacyclic triterpenoid, has been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, contributing to its potential in alleviating BPH symptoms. Flavonoids such as kaempferol and quercetin, present in Pygeum africanum, have been demonstrated to possess anti-androgenic activity, which may help in reducing the size of the enlarged prostate. The combination of these constituents likely contributes to the plant's efficacy in managing BPH symptoms, including improved urinary flow and reduced nocturia. These compounds have been isolated and characterized through various studies, providing a scientific basis for the potential therapeutic benefits of Pygeum africanum.",
