    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Pygeum africanum are tincture, capsules, tea, infusion, and pygeum extract. These preparations are made from the bark of the African cherry tree, Prunus africana, and are used to support prostate health due to their content of beta-sitosterol, a phytosterol with anti-inflammatory properties. Pygeum extract, often standardized to 5-10% of the active compound, is a concentrated form of the herb and is commonly used in supplements to alleviate symptoms of benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). Capsules and tinctures are also used to provide a standardized dose of pygeum, while tea and infusion are made by steeping the bark in hot water to create a beverage. The use of these herbal preparations has been studied in clinical trials, with results showing improvement in urinary flow and reduction in symptoms of BPH.",
