    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Pygeum africanum improperly include experiencing nausea and dizziness due to the potential interaction with other medications or pre-existing medical conditions. Improper use may also exacerbate benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) symptoms as Pygeum africanum is primarily used to alleviate BPH symptoms. Suffering from diarrhea is another possible side effect as Pygeum africanum may increase the risk of gastrointestinal side effects in some individuals. Additionally, aggravating hypotension is a concern as Pygeum africanum may lower blood pressure, which can be problematic for individuals with pre-existing hypotension. These side effects can occur if Pygeum africanum is taken in high doses or combined with other medications without proper medical supervision."
